CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc-bq.pancancer_atlas.Original_TCGA_RPPA_pancan_clean`
(
  AliquotBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA aliquot barcode, eg TCGA-12-1089-01A-01D-0517-28"),
  Study STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/tcga-study-abbreviations"),
  Protein STRING OPTIONS(description="Protein symbol and phosphorylation status (if applicable), eg P53, JNK_pT183Y185"),
  Value FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Expression level of protein as measured by reverse-phase protein arrays (RPPAs).Examples: 0.204238725,-0.01826295")
)
OPTIONS(
  friendly_name="PanCancer RPPA Final",
  description="Data loaded from the PanCancer Atlas initiative on the GDC in April 2018. Contains normalized and batch corrected data of protein concentration, generated using the reverse phase protein array (RPPA) platform.  \n\nMore details:  https://gdc.cancer.gov/about-data/publications/PanCan-CellOfOrigin, file:TCGA-RPPA-pancan-clean.txt. \n\nFor data annotated with pertinent TCGA Barcodes and filtered by the barcode white list, table Filtered_TCGA_RPPA_pancan_clean is recommended.",
  labels=[("category", "processed_-omics_data"), ("status", "current"), ("access", "open"), ("source_0", "gdc"), ("data_type", "protein_expression"), ("program", "pancancer_atlas"), ("reference_genome", "hg19"), ("source_1", "literature")]
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc-bq.pancancer_atlas.Filtered_MC3_MAF_V5_one_per_tumor_sample`
(
  ParticipantBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA barcode identifier for the study participant, eg TCGA-02-0001"),
  Tumor_SampleBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Original TCGA tumor sample barcode.TCGA-WC-A885-01A, TCGA-HQ-A2OF-01A."),
  Tumor_AliquotBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Original TCGA tumor aliquote barcode. Examples: TCGA-WC-A885-01A,TCGA-XF-AAN3-01A"),
  Normal_SampleBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Sample Barcode For The Normal Tissue. Examples: TCGA-V4-A9EI-10A, TCGA-V4-A9EI-10A"),
  Normal_AliquotBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Aliquot Barcode For The Normal Tissue. Examples: TCGA-CR-7385-10A-01D-2013-08, TCGA-DX-A3M1-10A-01D-A22A-09"),
  Normal_SampleTypeLetterCode STRING OPTIONS(description="Sample Type Letter Code. The subset of 4 values currently used are: NBC, NB, NT, NBM. See https://Gdc.Cancer.Gov/Resources-Tcga-Users/Tcga-Code-Tables/Sample-Type-Codes"),
  Study STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/tcga-study-abbreviations"),
  Hugo_Symbol STRING OPTIONS(description="HUGO symbol for the gene (HUGO symbols are always in all caps). \"Unknown\" is used for regions that do not correspond to a gene"),
  HGVSp_Short STRING OPTIONS(description="Protein sequence of the variant in HGVS recommended format, but using 1-letter amino-acid codes. \"p.=\" signifies no change in the protein"),
  Variant_Classification STRING OPTIONS(description="Translational effect of variant allele; eg. Missense_Mutation, Nonsense_Mutation, etc."),
  HGVSc STRING OPTIONS(description="The coding sequence of the variant in HGVS recommended format"),
  CENTERS STRING OPTIONS(description="One or more genome sequencing center reporting the variant"),
  FILTER STRING OPTIONS(description="List of failed filters (if any), or \"PASS\" indicating the variant has passed all filters.")
)
OPTIONS(
  friendly_name="PanCancer Filtered Merged MAF",
  description="Extracted from the PanCancer Atlas initiative on the GDC in Sept 2016 (file name pancan.merged.v0.2.5.filtered.maf.gz). Contains Somatic mutation calls.    \n\nNote: Data was filtered such that the only rows with the Variant_Classification in {Frame_Shift_Del, Frame_Shift_Ins, In_Frame_Del, In_Frame_Ins, Missense_Mutation, Nonsense_Mutation, Nonstop_Mutation, Splice_Site, Translation_Start_Site} were retained (Consistent with e.g. ISB, MSKCC, Broad definition of mutated gene). Moreover, Additional annotations were added (e.g. ParticipantBarcode). FPPP project aliquots were removed, and Rows with a solid tissue normal reference were removed if a corresponding blood derived normal reference was available.   \n\nMore details https://gdc.cancer.gov/about-data/publications/PanCan-MYC-2018",
  labels=[("category", "processed_-omics_data"), ("status", "current"), ("access", "open"), ("source_0", "gdc"), ("data_type", "somatic_mutation"), ("program", "pancancer_atlas"), ("reference_genome", "hg19"), ("source_1", "literature")]
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc-bq.pancancer_atlas.Filtered_EBpp_AdjustPANCAN_IlluminaHiSeq_RNASeqV2_genExp`
(
  ParticipantBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA barcode identifier for the study participant, eg TCGA-02-0001"),
  SampleBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Barcode of the biospecimen sample, eg TCGA-13-1489-02A"),
  AliquotBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA aliquot barcode, eg TCGA-12-1089-01A-01D-0517-28"),
  SampleTypeLetterCode STRING OPTIONS(description="Letter code of the sample type using the TCGA standards, eg TPN, EBV. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/sample-type-codes"),
  SampleType STRING OPTIONS(description="There are 10 sample types: Blood Derived Normal, Primary solid Tumor, Solid Tissue Normal, Recurrent Solid Tumor, Metastatic, Additional - New Primary, Primary Blood Derived Cancer - Peripheral Blood, Buccal Cell Normal, Additioanal Metastatic, Bone Marrrow Normal"),
  Study STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/tcga-study-abbreviations"),
  Symbol STRING OPTIONS(description="eg TP53, LRP1B, etc (same as Hugo_Symbol field except blank instead of Unknown"),
  Entrez STRING OPTIONS(description="Entrez ID from the NCBI, eg 730971"),
  normalized_count FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Normalized gene expression")
)
OPTIONS(
  friendly_name="PanCancer Filtered RNA Final",
  description="Data extracted from the PanCancer Atlas initiative on the GDC in April 2018. Contains batch normalized RNASeqV2 mRNA data annotated with pertinent TCGA Barcodes.  \n\nNote: the data was extracted from the BigQuery Table isb-cgc:pancancer_atlas.EBpp_AdjustPANCAN_IlluminaHiSeq_RNASeqV2_genExp. The table was annotated with pertinent TCGA Barcodes, and participants were subsequently filtered using the PanCancer Atlas whitelist (table Whitelist_ParticipantBarcodes ).  \n\nMore details: BigQuery table: isb-cgc-bq:pancancer_atlas.Original_EBpp_AdjustPANCAN_IlluminaHiSeq_RNASeqV2_genExp and https://gdc.cancer.gov/about-data/publications/pancanatlas",
  labels=[("access", "open"), ("category", "processed_-omics_data"), ("data_type", "gene_expression"), ("program", "pancancer_atlas"), ("reference_genome", "hg19"), ("source_0", "gdc"), ("source_1", "literature"), ("status", "current")]
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc-bq.pancancer_atlas.Filtered_clinical_PANCAN_patient_with_followup`
(
  bcr_patient_uuid STRING OPTIONS(description="Patient universally unique identifier, eg 180A2B9C-9CAC-4D96-86E8-CD6B3B9386B5"),
  bcr_patient_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA barcode identifier for the study participant, eg TCGA-02-0001"),
  acronym STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/tcga-study-abbreviations"),
  gender STRING OPTIONS(description="Participant gender; eg. MALE, FEMALE"),
  vital_status STRING OPTIONS(description="The latest updated vital status from follow-up data, eg Alive, Dead, [Discrepancy], NULL"),
  days_to_birth FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Days since birth (a negative value, relative to the date of diagnosis which is considered to be t=0)"),
  days_to_death STRING OPTIONS(description="If vital_status indicates 'dead', then this is the number of days to death (a positive value) relative to the date of diagnosis."),
  days_to_last_followup STRING OPTIONS(description="If vital_status indicates 'alive', then this is the number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last followup (communication contact)."),
  days_to_initial_pathologic_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="The number of days to initial pathologic diagnosis"),
  age_at_initial_pathologic_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="Age, in years, at which a condition or disease was first diagnosed"),
  icd_10 STRING OPTIONS(description="Alphanumeric value used to describe the disease code from the tenth version of the International Classification of Disease (ICD-10). Examples: C01, C55, C40.3"),
  tissue_retrospective_collection_indicator STRING OPTIONS(description="Text indicator for the time frame of tissue procurement, indicating that the tissue was obtained and stored prior to the initiation of the project. Takes YES, NO, NULL, and [Discrepancy] values."),
  icd_o_3_histology STRING OPTIONS(description="Code that represents the histology of the disease using the third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000, used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms"),
  tissue_prospective_collection_indicator STRING OPTIONS(description="Text indicator for the time frame of tissue procurement, indicating that the tissue was procured in parallel to the project. Takes YES, NO, NULL, and [Discrepancy] values."),
  history_of_neoadjuvant_treatment STRING OPTIONS(description="Possible values: Yes, No,Yes - Pharmaceutical Treatmet Prior to Resection, Yes - Radiation Prior to Resection(also can be blank)"),
  icd_o_3_site STRING OPTIONS(description="Code that represents the site of the disease using the third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000, used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms. Examples:C01.9, C20.9, C32.1"),
  tumor_tissue_site STRING OPTIONS(description="Category describing current smoking status and smoking history as self-reported by a participant.; eg. 1, 2, etc."),
  new_tumor_event_after_initial_treatment STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether a patient has had a new tumor event after initial treatment; Yes, No"),
  radiation_therapy STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether a patient has had radiation therapy; YES, NO, NULL, [Unknown], and [Discrepancy]"),
  race STRING OPTIONS(description="The race of a participant, independent from ethnicity; eg. White, Black or African American, Asian, Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander, American Indian or Alaska Native"),
  project_code STRING OPTIONS(description="Project code; TCGA or NULL"),
  prior_dx STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator and type of prior diagnosis; eg. No; Yes, History of Prior Malignancy; Yes, History of Synchronous/Bilateral Malignancy; Both History of Synchronous/Bilateral and Prior Malignancy, [Discrepancy], and NULL"),
  disease_code STRING OPTIONS(description="A code representing the type of cancer. Values can be found at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/tcga-study-abbreviations; eg. OV, GBM, LUAD"),
  ethnicity STRING OPTIONS(description="The ethnic origination of a participant, independent from race; eg. Not Hispanic or Latino, Hispanic or Latino"),
  informed_consent_verified STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether informed consent is verified; YES"),
  person_neoplasm_cancer_status STRING OPTIONS(description="The participant's cancer status; Either WITH TUMOR or TUMOR FREE, [Unknown], [Discrepancy], and NULL"),
  patient_id STRING OPTIONS(description="Participant ID; eg. AA2W, AA2T"),
  year_of_initial_pathologic_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="Four digit year of the initial pathologic diagnosis"),
  histological_type STRING OPTIONS(description="The histological type of cancer; eg. Adenosquamous, Astrocytoma, etc."),

  form_completion_date STRING OPTIONS(description="Form completion date; eg. 2013-12-23"),

  pathologic_N STRING OPTIONS(description="The pathologic N score is a rating of the extent of cancer within nearby lymph nodes, based on surgery or biopsy; eg. N1, N2, N3"),
  system_version STRING OPTIONS(description="System version; eg. 2009, 4th"),
  pathologic_stage STRING OPTIONS(description="The stage of the cancer, based on surgery or biopsy; eg. Stage II, Stage III, Stage IV, Stage IVA, Stage IIIB, Stage IIIS, Stage IIIC"),
  stage_other STRING OPTIONS(description="Other stages of cancer; this field is NULL for all rows"),

  OS INT64 OPTIONS(description="Overall survival event, 1 for death from any cause, 0 for alive"),
  OS_time INT64 OPTIONS(description="Overall survival time in days, last_contact_days_to or death_days_to, whichever is larger"),
  DSS INT64 OPTIONS(description="Disease-specific survival event, 1 for patient whose vital_status was Dead and tumor_status was WITH TUMOR. This is not a 100% accurate definition but is the best we could do with this dataset. Technically a patient could be with tumor but died of a car accident and therefore incorrectly considered as an event."),
  DSS_time INT64 OPTIONS(description="Disease-specific survival time in days, last_contact_days_to or death_days_to, whichever is larger."),
  DFI INT64 OPTIONS(description="Disease-free interval event, 1 for patient having new tumor event whether it is a local recurrence, distant metastasis, new primary tumor of the cancer, including cases with a new tumor event whose type is N/A.  Disease free was defined by: first, treatment_outcome_first_course is \"Complete Remission/Response\"; if the tumor type doesn't have \"treatment_outcome_first_course\" then disease-free was defined by the value \"R0\" in the field of \"residual_tumor\"; otherwise, disease-free was defined by the value \"negative\" in the field of \"margin_status\". If the tumor type did not have any of these fields, then its DFI was NA. 0 for censored otherwise. New primary tumor in other organ was censored; patients who were Dead with tumor without new tumor event are excluded; patients wih stage IV are excluded too."),
  DFI_time INT64 OPTIONS(description="Disease-free interval time in days, new_tumor_event_dx_days_to for events, or for censored cases, either last_contact_days_to or death_days_to, whichever is applicable."),

"),
  PFI_time INT64 OPTIONS(description="Progression-free interval time in days, for events, either new_tumor_event_dx_days_to or death_days_to,  whichever is applicable; or for censored cases, either last_contact_days_to or death_days_to, whichever is applicable"),
  Redaction STRING OPTIONS(description="To show if the case is redacted.")
)

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc-bq.pancancer_atlas.Filtered_all_CNVR_data_by_gene`
(
  ParticipantBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA barcode identifier for the study participant, eg TCGA-02-0001"),
  SampleBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Barcode of the biospecimen sample, eg TCGA-13-1489-02A"),
  AliquotBarcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA aliquot barcode, eg TCGA-12-1089-01A-01D-0517-28"),
  SampleTypeLetterCode STRING OPTIONS(description="Letter code of the sample type using the TCGA standards, eg TPN, EBV. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/sample-type-codes"),
  SampleType STRING OPTIONS(description="There are 10 sample types: Blood Derived Normal, Primary solid Tumor, Solid Tissue Normal, Recurrent Solid Tumor, Metastatic, Additional - New Primary, Primary Blood Derived Cancer - Peripheral Blood, Buccal Cell Normal, Additioanal Metastatic, Bone Marrrow Normal"),
  Study STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-tcga-users/tcga-code-tables/tcga-study-abbreviations"),
  Gene_Symbol STRING OPTIONS(description="eg TP53, LRP1B, etc (same as Hugo_Symbol field except blank instead of Unknown"),
  Locus_ID INT64 OPTIONS(description="Gene locus ID, eg.  57380, 100616303"),
  Cytoband STRING OPTIONS(description="Full cytoband name, including chromosome. E.g, 17p13.2 See https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Class/MLACourse/Original8Hour/Genetics/chrombanding.html"),
  GISTIC_Calls FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Gistic Copy Number calls")
)

  description="Data extracted from the PanCancer Atlas initiative on the GDC in Aug 2016.   labels=[("category", "processed_-omics_data"), ("status", "current"), ("access", "open"), ("source_0", "gdc"), ("data_type", "copy_number_segment_masked"), ("program", "pancancer_atlas"), ("reference_genome", "hg19"), ("source_1", "literature")]
);
